<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT February 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA -- At least eight people have been confirmed killed and
30 others injured as two avalanches roared through a ski resort in
Austria's western state of Triol on Tuesday evening, the Austrian
news media reported.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 people went missing while rescuers are continuing the
searching work.
</P>
<P>
Both avalanches rushed down the Alps to the Galtuer resort
nestling in the Paznauntal valley after 4 p.m. local time (1500
GMT). The snow wall, five meters high and 800 meters long, tore
through 10 houses and buried 50 people. (Austria-Avalanches-Death)
</P>
