</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Central American foreign ministers will meet here on
Friday to prepare for a summit meeting of regional heads of state
with U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The summit meeting was slated for March 12 in Guatemala and the
participating heads of state will examine questions of regional
interest, said Nicaraguan Foreign Minister Eduardo Montealegre.
</P>
<P>
Clinton will come to Nicaragua on March 8 on the first stage of
his Central American tour, which will also take him to Guatemala
and Honduras. (Central America-Clinton-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski on Tuesday
signed a law to ratify the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The treaty, adopted at the United Nations General Assembly on
September 10, 1996, bans any nuclear test, restricts the upgrade
of nuclear weaponry or the improvement of the nuclear weapons now
in service.
</P>
<P>
The treaty will go into effect 180 days after the ratification
of all the 44 countries known to have nuclear reactors, including
Poland. (Poland-Ratify-Nuclear Treaty)
</P>
<P>
